# <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# │       │             │
# │       │             └─⫸ Imperative, lowercase. "add foo", not "added foo".
# │       │
# │       └─⫸ Scope (optional). One of:
# │             cli | vsc-plugin | jetbrains-plugin | shared | workflow | meta | deps
# │
# └─⫸ Type (required). One of:
#       feat      → ✨  Added section of the changelog
#       fix       → 🐛  Fixed section
#       refactor  → 🔧  Changed section
#       perf      → ⚡  Performance section
#       docs      → 📝  Documentation section
#       build     → 🔨  Build section
#       ci        → 🤖  CI section
#       test      → 🧪  Tests section
#       chore     → 🧹  Chore section
#       style     → 🎨  skipped from changelog (formatting only)
#
# Append "!" for breaking changes: feat(cli)!: drop Node 18 support
# Or add "BREAKING CHANGE: …" in the footer.
#
# <empty line>
#
# <body — optional>
# Explain *why* this change is needed, not *what* it does.
# Wrap at 72 chars. Leave a blank line between summary and body.
#
# <empty line>
#
# <footer — optional>
# BREAKING CHANGE: <short description of incompatible change>
# Fixes: #<issue>
# Refs: #<issue>
#
# ── Examples ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   feat(cli): add --skip-pair flag to start without a prior pair step
#
#   fix(vsc-plugin): prevent duplicate terminal after auto-update
#
#   refactor(shared): collapse MODEL_PRICING tables into @codeagent/shared
#
#   feat(cli)!: drop Node 18 support
#
#       The npm tarball still works on Node 18 at runtime but the test
#       suite and build tools now require Node 20. Users on Node 18
#       should upgrade before installing this release.
#
#       BREAKING CHANGE: minimum Node version raised to 20.
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
